{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17609855","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17609855"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:52:01+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:52:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16128"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16128","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16128"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.31,0.17,0.38,0.03,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8819"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114310"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8819","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8819"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16128"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96310"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"7031"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21038"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21041"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114310","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114310"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring embryological development, several structures contribute to the formation of external genitalia.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following embryological structures gives rise to the labia majora in females?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Urogenital folds","Urethral folds","Labioscrotal swellings","Cloacal fold","Genital tubercle"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Elabioscrotal swellings\u003C/strong\u003E develop into the labia majora in females. In males, these same structures fuse in the midline to form the scrotum.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUrogenital folds\u003C/strong\u003E develop into the labia minora in females. \u003Cstrong\u003EUrethral folds\u003C/strong\u003E contribute to penile urethral development in males but are not involved in female external genitalia. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ecloacal fold\u003C/strong\u003E contributes to formation of the urogenital and anal membranes. The \u003Cstrong\u003Egenital tubercle\u003C/strong\u003E develops into the clitoris in females and the glans penis in males.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis demonstrates how common embryological structures differentiate along different developmental pathways to form sex-specific anatomical structures.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The labioscrotal swellings develop into the labia majora in females and the scrotum in males.","The urogenital folds form the labia minora in females.","External genitalia development follows different pathways in males and females from common embryological structures."],"references":["Cunha GR, Baskin LS. Development of the external genitalia. Differentiation. 2020 Mar-Apr;112:7-9. doi: 10.1016/j.diff.2019.10.008. Epub 2019 Dec 4. PMID: 31881402; PMCID: PMC7138693.","Nguyen JD, Duong H. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis: Female External Genitalia. [Updated 2023 Jul 25]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK547703/","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96310"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16128"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions"